---
const highlights = [
  'Frontend Development',
  'Developer Relations',
  'Public Speaking',
  'Community Building',
];
---

<section id="about" class="py-8 px-6 md:py-20 bg-muted/30">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto space-y-6 md:space-y-10">
    <div class="space-y-2">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium text-foreground sm:text-4xl">About Me</h2>
      <div class="w-20 h-1 bg-primary rounded-full"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground sm:space-y-6 sm:text-lg">
      <p>
        I'm a frontend developer passionate about creating meaningful web experiences that make a difference.
        My journey in tech is driven by curiosity and a genuine love for building things that work.
      </p>
      <p>
        Beyond writing code, I'm deeply invested in developer relations and community building.
        I believe in the power of sharing knowledge, whether through speaking at conferences,
        leading workshops, or contributing to open-source communities.
      </p>
      <p>
        Teaching and learning in public is at the heart of what I do. I explore technology through
        real-world collaboration, constantly seeking opportunities to grow while helping others on their journey.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      {
        highlights.map((highlight) => (
          <span class="px-3 py-1.5 text-sm sm:px-5 sm:py-2.5 sm:text-base bg-secondary/20 backdrop-blur-sm border border-secondary/30 rounded-lg text-foreground shadow-sm hover:bg-secondary/30 transition-all">
            {highlight}
          </span>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
